% if: executable(poetry)

Poetry - Adding Dependencies

Manage dependencies in your Python project with [prgm]poetry[/prgm]. Use the [prgm]add[/prgm] subcommand to add new dependencies.

$ [prgm]poetry add[/prgm] [arg-value]package[/arg-value]
$ [prgm]poetry add[/prgm] [arg]--group[/arg]=[arg-value]GROUP_NAME[/arg-value] [arg-value]package_name[/arg-value]

Package Sources

- A [cyan]name[/cyan], with an optional constraint ([magenta]requests[/magenta], [magenta]requests@^2.3.0[/magenta])
- A [cyan]git repository[/cyan] ([magenta]git+ssh://...[/magenta], [magenta]git+https://...[/magenta])
- A [cyan]revision[/cyan] of a git repository ([magenta]git+ssh://...#refspec[/magenta])
- A [cyan]wheel[/cyan] ([magenta]my-package.whl[/magenta])
- A [cyan]directory[/cyan] ([magenta]my-package/[/magenta])
- A [cyan]tarball[/cyan] ([magenta]https://.../my-package.tar.gz[/magenta])
